Thanks to all the students who responded. Here are some of the catchy headlines that we received:  

“Friends and Financials -- Is There a Correlation?” by Deepti of Edison Academy; 
"Where Your Friends Are, So Is Your Income Level Also" by Sophie of Mesa, Arizona; 
“Based on Income, Where Do You Find Your Friends?” by Drew of Kentwood, Michigan;
“Friends by Chance or Friends by Income” by Audrey of Reno, Nevada and 
“Friendships Forged by Money or Bonding?” by Sebastian of California.

You can continue to post responses. Please check back by Friday, Feb. 10 to see the Reveal with the free link to the original New York Times article, some questions about this graph and a few Stat Nuggets.

The next “What’s Going On In This Graph?” will be released by Friday, Feb. 10 with moderation on Wednesday, Feb. 15. The topic – the human population since 11,700 years ago.   

Signing off – Sharon Hessney from Boston, who met most of her friends at work and thinks she may be an outlier, and Luke Wilcox from Kentwood, Michigan who feels lucky to have so many friends at such an old age.

